Police were alerted to Dobbies Garden Centre in Rougham Road after a suspected explosive device was discovered nearby. A bomb disposal team from the Army in Colchester were rushed to the scene.  The garden centre was evacuated while the team investigated and a cordon was put in place. The army team carried out a controlled explosion on the device after moving it to a safe location. A Suffolk Police spokesman said a member of the public alerted them to the suspected unexploded ordnance at about 8am. He said: "A suspected device was reported to police by a member of the public just before 8am. Near to Dobbies. No road closures. The EOD (Explosive Ordnance Disposal) team from Army, Colchester, is on the scene. "Planning to move device to a safer location." The garden centre has since reopened.